From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MC20018 <winme2001@outlook.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 18:14:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Complete fine-grained ecosystem event hooks

Add vanilla hook points for the next set of high-value ecosystem events, including player pre-login, armor stand manipulation, book edits, egg throws, level changes, velocity updates, main-hand changes, statistic increments, recipe discovery, block can-build checks, multi-place operations, block cooking, furnace start smelt, structure growth, portal enter/exit/create details, target living entity changes, block damage sources, and block/entity combust sources.

Keep patched Minecraft code thin by routing event construction, cancellation semantics, mutable payload application, and listener failure handling through Fand bridge helpers. Preserve cancellable structure growth by snapshotting generated blocks and restoring both block states and Fand block components when listeners cancel.

